channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Deadline has passed for Columbia students to leave encampment
item.description: The deadline set by Columbia University for demonstrators to vacate an encampment there or face suspension has passed. Follow for live updates.

item.title: Oregon Lottery announces 3 winners of $1.326 billion Powerball ticket
item.description: The staggering $1.326 billion Powerball ticket was the fourth-largest Powerball jackpot in history and the eighth-largest among U.S. jackpot games.

item.title: Mark David Chapman Fast Facts
item.description: Read CNN's Mark David Chapman Fast Facts and learn more about the life of the man who killed musician John Lennon.

item.title: Upstate NY district attorney 'so sorry' for cursing at officer who tried to ticket her for speeding
item.description: An upstate New York district attorney has apologized after police video showed her cursing at an officer who tried to give her a speeding ticket

item.title: April 28, 2024 - US university protests
item.description: Pro-Palestinian protests continue at major US universities, and several schools have called police to remove demonstrators.

item.title: 'Vampire facials' were linked to cases of HIV. Here's what to know about the beauty treatment
item.description: The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention issued a report last week that documented the first instances of HIV transmissions contracted through unsterile injections used while receiving “vampire facials,” cosmetic procedures involving microneedling

item.title: April 27, 2024 - Campus protest updates
item.description: Pro-Palestinian protests continue at major US universities, where several schools have called police on protesters, leading to the arrests of hundreds across the country. Follow for live updates.

item.title: College protests live updates: Columbia protesters defy 2 p.m. deadline to disperse
item.description: Protests have broken out at colleges and universities across the country in connection with the war in Gaza.

item.title: April 26, 2024 - Protests at Columbia and other schools escalate
item.description: Pro-Palestinian protests continue at major US universities where several schools have called police on protesters, leading to the arrests of hundreds across the country. Follow for live updates.

item.title: Zebras get loose near highway exit, gallop into Washington community before most are corralled
item.description: There were many people doing double takes Sunday in North Bend, Washington, after four zebras got loose from their trailer and galloped into a neighborhood
